{ @@HeaderStart@@Introduction@@HeaderEnd@@The Ruy Lopez is the Rolls-Royce of classical chess openings.  Every single World-Champion to date has played this opening extensively, oftentimes with both colors.    @@StartBlockQuote@@I put great stake in the Ruy Lopez: I like it, feel it, and understand it - Anatoly Karpov@@EndBlockQuote@@It’s no accident that many of the lines bear the names of these great champions, ranging from the evergreen Steinitz complex to the Karpov and Smyslov variations in the Zaitsev.   @@StartBlockQuote@@The Ruy Lopez occupied a constant place in my opening repertoire. In it is reflected the classical interpretation of the problem of the center. - Vasily Smyslov@@EndBlockQuote@@Moreover, many matches for the ultimate chess title were decided in this very opening. Kasparov was unable to break through Kramnik’s Berlin wall, which brought his dominant reign to an end. The 16th world champion, Magnus Carlsen, is renowned for squeezing the life out of his opponents in the subtletities of the Spanish structures.   Studying the fascinating strategic and tactical intricacies of this opening will pay dividends for the aspiring amateur.   The popularity of the Spanish opening has inevitably led to a wealth of opening theory. However, aided by the latest versions of Stockfish and Leela running on superfast cloud hardware, we've discovered a treasure trove of novelties and never-before-seen plans. These will not only put your opponents against the ropes but also shortcut large amounts of inferior lines.  The repertoire in this course is both practical and ambitious. It was designed to put maximum pressure on Black’s position without overwhelming you with 100s upon 100s of variations.  While theoretical knowledge is important to fight for an advantage, understanding the key middlegame themes is paramount. We did not just want to give you lines to learn and then leave you on your own to figure out the middlegame plans and tactical motifs.  To this end, an entirechapter on must-know strategic themes, typical plans, and pawn structures was included. You will also findreference games showcasing these ideas in action. Finally, a chapter with commontactical puzzles in the Ruy Lopez is also included.  Thequickstarter guide was created to get you playing the Ruy Lopez in no time. Once you have completed it, we recommend learning the mostimportant lines and only then the full repertoire. Finally, you can test your knowledge of critical nuances and move orders with the aid ofmemory markers. }
