[Result "*"]
[FEN "r3r1k1/1b1nqpbp/p2p1np1/2pPp3/1pP1P3/PP3NNP/2B2PP1/R1BQR1K1 w - - 0 19"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ The following game segment showcases another must-know kingside attacking resource - the f5 knight sacrifice. }
19. Nh4 Qd8 20. Nhf5
{ Thematic and difficult to meet in practice!   Slow-playing it with  20.Be3  likely followed by Qd2, Kh1, and Rg1 was another viable plan. }
20... gxf5 21. Nxf5 Nf8
{ Correct, Black must bring new forces to the kingside to weather White's attack.   21...Bf8?  is way too slow. After  22.g4+-  -g5, Kh1 and Qh5 will soon land on the board with decisive effect. }
22. axb4 cxb4 23. Qd2 { White's queen is ready to scoot over to the kingside. }
23... a5
{ Natural but incorrect, a good example of how it's difficult to defend versus a kingside attack.   23...Bc8!  attempting to neutralize the f5 knight, White's main attacker, was the way to go!  24.Nxg7   24.Qxb4?  is nonsense as after  24...Bxf5  25.exf5  a5-+  White has no attack and is simply a piece down.  24...Kxg7  25.f4   25.Qxb4  still makes little sense. Following  25...Ng6⇆  Black will be the one attacking with ...Rg8 and ...Kh8 to follow.  25...exf4  26.Qxf4  Ng6  27.Qh6+  Kh8  28.Bg5  Qb6+  29.Be3  Qd8  30.e5!?  opening up the light-squared bishop and intending Rf1 next. The position remains unclear with chances for both sides. }
24. Qg5
{ 24.Nxg7?  was a big mistake, after which White's attack fizzled out and Black eventually managed to win in the game 0-1 Karjakin, S @@StartBracket@@2694@@EndBracket@@ - Roiz, M @@StartBracket@@2644@@EndBracket@@ EU-chT @@StartBracket@@Men@@EndBracket@@ 16th Ukraine-Isreal 2007:  24...Kxg7  25.Qh6+  Kh8  26.Bg5  N8d7!  27.f4  Rg8  28.fxe5  Rg6  29.Qh4  Nxe5  30.Rf1  Qb6+  31.Kh1  Nfd7  32.Rf5  Rag8  33.Re1  a4!  34.bxa4  b3  35.Bb1  f6  36.Be3  Qb4  37.Rh5  R8g7  38.Bh6  Rf7  39.Qf2  Ba6  40.Rg1  Bxc4  41.Qf5  Qxa4  42.Qe6  Qa6  43.Bf4  Nc5  44.Qf5  Kg8  45.Be3  Bd3  0-1 }
24... Ng6 25. Nxg7 Kxg7 26. Qh6+ Kh8 27. Bg5
{ Harry the h-pawn is about to come rolling down the board with a big attack. I can't imagine anyone liking Black's chances here. }
