{ The following game is a great example on how to take Black on when the second player expands prematurely on the queenside. Key themes include fighting for the a-file and targeting Black's weaknesses on this flank. }
1. Nf3
{ White started with Nf3 but the game soon transposed into the Ruy Lopez. }
1... Nc6 2. e4 e5 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 O-O
9. h3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 Qc7 12. d5 c4
{ A premature queenside expansion that was strongly met by } 13. b4
{ This pawn advance completely nullifies any queenside play Black ever had in store. }
13... cxb3
{ 13...Nb7  14.a4  Bd7  15.a5!  would completely block off the queenside, giving White a free hand on the kingside. }
14. axb3 Bd7 15. Ba3 { A natural developing move, threatening the nifty Nxe5! }
15... Bd8
{ 15...Rfe8  is no good on account of  16.Nxe5  dxe5  17.Bxe7  Rxe7  18.d6+- }
16. Bd3 Nb7 { Black's knight is headed to c5 but White is having none of it. }
17. b4
{ Echoes of theKarpov-Unzicker game, White completely restricts the b7 knight. The a3 bishop is also blocked but can be easily rerouted to e3. Black's knight on b7, however, has no prospects whatsoever. }
17... Be7 18. Bc1 Rfc8 19. Re2
{ The ROVER @@StartBracket@@rook up and over@@EndBracket@@ is a thematic way of doubling up on the a-file. Well worth remembering! }
19... a5
{ 19...h6?  loses by force to  20.Rea2  Qb6  21.Be3  Qd8  22.Rxa6+-  wins the a6-pawn and the game. }
20. Rea2 { White doubles up on the a-file just in time! } 20... Qd8 21. Be3
axb4
{ Opening up the queenside leaves Black with a weak pawn on b5. This weakness will be the second player's undoing. }
22. cxb4 Rxa2 23. Rxa2 Ra8 24. Qe2 g6 25. Nc3
{ Now there's no saving the b5 pawn. } 25... Rxa2 26. Qxa2 Qc7
{ 26...Qe8  fails to save the b5 pawn due to  27.Qa6+-  hitting the b7 knight and b5 pawn again. }
27. Nxb5 Bxb5 28. Bxb5 Nxe4 29. Qa7
{ Faced with the threat of Ba6, Black resigned. There's no way to save the b7 knight.   1-0 @@StartBracket@@29@@EndBracket@@ Morovic Fernandez,I  @@StartBracket@@2580@@EndBracket@@-Eid,F @@StartBracket@@2387@@EndBracket@@ Khanty-Mansiysk 2010 }
