{ Black is about to bring his knight to f4 with ...Ng6-f4. Find White's best move. }
12. f4
{ Black seemed to have the f4 square on lockdown but not quite! The unprotected queen on f6 makes this breakthrough possible. }
12... gxf4
{ 12...Bc5+  13.Be3  Bxe3+  14.Nxe3  Ng6?   14...gxf4  was necessary. Even so, after  15.Ng4±  the e5 pawn drops.  15.fxe5  Qe7  16.d4+-  Black is a clean pawn down with the worse position. He quickly lost following...  16...Nf4  17.Rae1  h5  18.Nf5  Qe6  19.h4  Ng6  20.hxg5  Kb8  21.Qb3  Qd7  22.c3  Rdf8  23.Nh6  Rh7  24.Rf6  h4  25.Ref1  h3  26.Rxg6  1-0 @@StartBracket@@26@@EndBracket@@ Wegerle,J @@StartBracket@@2451@@EndBracket@@-Schoppmeyer,J @@StartBracket@@1893@@EndBracket@@ Einhausen 2010 }
13. Bxf4
{ The e5 pawn will drop on the next turn. Black is in big trouble.   For example  13...Rhg8  14.Bxe5  Qg6  can be easily parried with  15.Rf2  covering g2 and noting that  15...Bc5  is easily blocked with  16.d4  Ba7  17.Re1+- }
