{ The following is a model game in the 4. d3 Anti-Berlin variation between Anand and Wesley So from the 2019 Tata Steel Rapid & Blitz. }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Bxc6 dxc6 6. Nbd2 Be6 7. O-O Bd6 8.
d4 Nd7 9. dxe5 Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Bxe5 11. f4 Bd4+ 12. Kh1 f5 13. Qh5+
{ At first sight, this may look like a spite check given Black can go ...g6. However, this queen sortie forces Black to weaken a bunch of dark squares in his camp. }
13... g6 14. Qe2 O-O 15. Nf3 Bf6
{ Black keeps the dark-squared bishops given all the weaknesses on this color complex. }
16. e5
{ Gains space and creates a protected passed pawn. White has a kingside pawn majority while Black can hardly create a passed pawn on the queenside. This means White will have a significant advantage in any ensuing endgames. }
16... Be7 17. Rd1 Qe8 18. Nd4 Qf7 19. Nxe6 Qxe6 20. Be3 Rad8
{ All the pieces are out and now it's time to improve our position. } 21. c4
{ White takes control over the d5 square, preventing Black from doubling up on the d-file. The first player will now seek to exchange all the rooks, getting one step closer to a winning endgame courtesy of the passed pawn on e5. }
21... a6 22. b3 Kf7 23. h3 h5 24. Bf2 Rxd1+ 25. Rxd1 Rd8 26. Rxd8 Bxd8 27. Qe1
{ Preparing Bh4 to swap yet another pair of pieces. Apart from trading all the pieces and reaching a winning pawn endgame, White can also try to penetrate Black's position with his queen. }
27... Qe7 { Black stops Bh4 at the cost of awkwardly placing his pieces. } 28.
Kh2 Ke6 29. Qd2 Qd7 { White declines the queen exchange and instead plays } 30.
Qb4
{ which comes with a double-attack, namely the threats of Qxb7 and Qf8-g8. }
30... Kf7
{ 30...b6  31.Qf8  Qe7  32.Qg8+  Kd7  33.Qxg6  Picks up a pawn with Black's remaining kingside pawns to fall shortly. }
31. Qxb7 { Anand had little trouble converting the extra pawn and easily won: }
31... Qd2 32. e6+
{ 32.Bg1  Qxf4+  33.Kh1  Qxe5  34.Qxa6+-  was also winning. White's a-pawn will be impossible to stop. }
32... Kg7
{ 32...Kxe6  does not work out for Black.  33.Qxc6+  Kf7  34.Qc5  Qxf4+  35.Bg3  The c7 pawn now drops.  35...Qd2  36.Bxc7  Bxc7+  37.Qxc7+  The passed c-pawn combined with Black's exposed king will easily decide the game. }
33. Bg1 Qxf4+ 34. Kh1 Qd6 35. Qxa6 Qxe6 36. Qa7 g5 37. a4 g4 38. Qe3 Qc8 39.
Qe8 gxh3 40. Bd4+ Kh6 41. Bf6 hxg2+ 42. Kxg2 f4 43. Qg8 Qd7 44. Qg5+ Kh7 45.
Qxh5+ Kg8 46. Qh8+ Kf7 47. Qg7+ Ke6 48. Qxd7+ Kxd7 49. Bxd8 Kxd8 50. Kf3
{ Black resigned in 1-0 @@StartBracket@@50@@EndBracket@@ Anand,V @@StartBracket@@2757@@EndBracket@@-So,W @@StartBracket@@2760@@EndBracket@@ Kolkata 2019. }
