{ Can you come with a plan for White? } 16. f5
{ White pushes ahead with f5 gaining a space advantage on the kingside. The plan is to expand on the kingside with g4-g5 and potentially even h4-h5-h6, intending to open the g and/or h-files for the rooks to penetrate Black's position. The second player has very little counterplay as his only pawn break with ... c5-c4 can be easily prevented with b2-b3. }
