1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bb4
{ Arguably the best out of all the irregular 3rd moves, although still pretty bad. Carlsen played it in a couple of blitz and online games with decent results so it deserves some attention. }
4. c3 Ba5 5. Qa4
{ 5.O-O  is White's most common move, but the text move is far simpler and stronger. }
5... Bb6 { 5...Nge7  drops a pawn after  6.Nxe5  Nxe5  7.Qxa5+- } 6. d4 Nf6 7.
