f5
{ This is practically forced since Black must keep the e-file closed.   8...Nd6  fails to  9.Bxc6  dxc6  10.Rxe5+  Kf8  11.c4+-  threatening to win material with c5. Black's position is in disarray.   8...d5  loses to  9.Bxc6+  bxc6  10.Qxc6++- }
9. Bxc6 dxc6
{ 9...bxc6??  loses the queen to  10.Rxe4!  fxe4  11.Bg5+-  Her majesty on g8 is trapped. }
10. Nxe5
{ I can't imagine anyone wanting this position with Black.   A sample continuation is  10...O-O  11.Qb3+  Qd5  12.f3  Nf6  13.Be3  Be6  14.Qc2±  threatening c4 is clearly better for White. }
