{ Goes after Black's only active piece. } 9... Bb6 10. Nxb6 axb6 11. Re1
{ We're not talking about enough compensation for the pawn, but rather a White advantage. We have the two bishops, more space and all our pieces will find good squares. Conversely, Black's position is very cramped and he will have a very hard time completing development. }
