9... Bf5 10. Bf4
{ 10.h3  Qe7  11.Bf4  was successfully played in1-0 @@StartBracket@@31@@EndBracket@@ Anand,V @@StartBracket@@2776@@EndBracket@@-L'Ami, E @@StartBracket@@2605@@EndBracket@@ Germany 2017 However, there's no need to spend a tempo on h3. }
10... Qe7 11. g4
{ Novel and strong, forcing Black's bishop back. The e4 pawn is now critically weak. }
11... Be6 12. Nd2 Nf6 13. Bg5
{ with the threat Nxe4. Black is under severe pressure.   A sample continuation is  13...Bd5  14.O-O  O-O-O   14...Bxe5?  only helps White.  15.dxe5  Qxe5  16.f4!  Qe7  17.c4  Bf7  18.Bxf6  Qxf6  19.Nxe4+-  with a decisive advantage.  15.c4  Bxe5  16.dxe5  Qxe5  17.Bxf6  Qxf6  18.cxd5  cxd5  19.Qe3±  Up next is f3 when Black doesn't have enough for the piece. }
