9. Bb3 Na5 10. Bg5
{ improves over the game1-0 @@StartBracket@@27@@EndBracket@@ Mortensen,E @@StartBracket@@2485@@EndBracket@@ -Bhandari,T Gausdal 1990. White is threatening to ruin Black's kingside pawn structure with Nxf6+. }
10... Nxb3 11. axb3 O-O 12. Nxf6+ gxf6 13. Bh6
{ Next up is Qg4 with a huge advantage. Black's kingside structure is in ruins and the king on g8 is very exposed. If that were not enough, the e4 pawn is also weak and can be targeted with Ne4. }
