{ Popular but bad as White can ignore this pawn and instead push ahead with }
6. e5
{ The pawn on e5 is a thorn in Black's position, depriving the g8 knight of the f6 square. You may be thinking Black's d4 pawn does an analogous job of restricting the b1 knight, but that is not the case as we can break with c3! }
