1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nge7
{ is known as the Cozio defense, the most established alternative to 3...a6 and a serious move that was recommended by GM Erwin L'Ami on Chessable.   With  3...Nge7  Black reinforces the knight so as to be able to meet  4.Bxc6  with  4...Nxc6  and thus avoid having to double the queenside pawns. This comes at the cost of the g8 knight being less active on e7 than f6 and restricting the f8 bishop, which will typically be fianchettoed after ...g6. }
4. Nc3
{ This natural move gives White good practical chances of getting an opening advantage. The plan is to expand in the center with d2-d4 on the next turn.   4.c3  isn't nearly as good here because of  4...d5!  5.Nxe5  dxe4=  Black is doing very well with ...Qd5 coming next. }
4... Ng6 5. h4
{ is White's most challenging move and a direct attempt at refuting Black's ...Ne7-g6 maneuver. }
5... Nd4 6. h5 Nf4
{ is quite a picturesque position. 6 moves in and Black's knights are well within enemy territory. }
7. Nxd4 exd4 8. Qf3 Bd6
{ is a key novelty proposed by GM Erwin L'ami in his Chessable course on the Cozio defense. }
9. Ne2 { Neutralizes Black's active knight. } 9... Nxe2
{ 9...Ne6  10.Bc4  O-O  11.h6±  is problematic for Black. } 10. Bxe2
{ White is now ready to force concessions with h6. Black should naturally stop this by playing }
10... h6 { himself. } 11. d3 a5
{ is a very deep waiting move. Black wants to see where White places his king, intending to only castle short after White does so. }
12. a3 a4
{ Black continues the waiting game. He's looking for White to castle short first, after which he'll follow suit. }
13. Qg4
{ is a timely moment to hit the g7 pawn taking advantage of the fact that ...O-O is impossible due to Bxh6. }
13... Be5 14. f4 Bf6 15. Qg3
{ White steps back with the queen introducing the threat of e5.   The immediate  15.e5  doesn't work because of  15...d6!  16.Qg3  dxe5  17.fxe5  Bg5  when Black's already taking over. }
15... d6
{ is one of the top choices of the engine. The machines assess all these positions as 0.00 but Black's moves are not easy to find. For example }
16. Bd2 O-O { This human move immediate lands Black in trouble after } 17. Qh2
{ clearing for a pawn storm with g4-g5. } *

