{ is my preferred move order. The plan is to develop the bishop to e3 before bringing out the b1 knight.   10.Nbd2  is White's main move, but it allows  10...exd4  11.cxd4  Nb4  a rather annoying move, threatening jump into d3. 10. Bc2 rules this out given that with the knight still on b1, the d3 square is safely guarded. }
