{ was played in a top-level correspondence game and is practically speaking also very good.   13.a4  is another interesting possibility. }
13... a5
{ Black can try to delay the ...f7-f5 break, but here comes a nice idea. } 14.
Bc1
{ Time to regroup the pieces. Black's last move signaled he is not willing to clash in the center immediately, so it makes perfect sense to start slowly regroup our pieces. }
14... a4
{ Black continues with his queenside expansion plan, further delaying ...f5. }
15. Ne3 Nf4 16. Nd5 Ne6 17. dxe5 Nxe5
{ 17...dxe5?  blunders the a4 pawn  18.Bxa4+− } 18. Nh2
{ An important move! White has more space and should thus avoid piece exchanges. It's hard to suggest a plan for Black. }
