1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Bxc6 dxc6 6. Nbd2 Bd6
{ is a tempo-up version of @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pppp1ppp/2n2n2/1B2p3/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 4 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Bxc6  dxc6  5.d3  Bd6  6.Nbd2  . This position featured in two high-profile games, namely Firouzja, A - Paravyan, D Lichess. org blitz 2020 and Hikaru, N - Carlsen, M Carlsen Tour Final rapid 2020. The extra tempo in the text is naturally in White's favor. }
7. Nc4 Qe7 8. a4
{ Novel and strong. White gains space on the queenside and prepares to pressure the e5 pawn with b3 followed by Bb2. }
8... O-O
{ 8...Bg4  is ineffective as White can immediately neutralize the pin  9.h3  Bh5  10.g4  Bg6  11.Nh4⩲  White has a slight edge due to the extra space and firm control over the f5 square. }
9. O-O Nd7 { is a move that Black will have to play sooner or later. } 10. b3
f6 11. Nh4
{ The f5-square is critically weak and a fantastic home for our knight. } 11...
Nb8 12. Nf5 Bxf5 13. exf5
{ White will slowly but surely start a kingside attack with Kh1, Rg1, g2-g4, and h2-h4. The first player only needs to watch out for ... e5-e4, which can be prevented with Nd2-e4. }
