{ Novel and strong, putting a lot of pressure on the e5 pawn.   The main point is that  8...exd4?!  is no good as the recapture  9.Qxd4  comes with a double-attack on the d6 bishop and g7 pawn. }
8... Qe7 9. O-O O-O 10. Re1
{ White is at least slightly better with superior central control and more active pieces. Two sample continuations are:   10...exd4?!  which runs into  11.Nxd6!  cxd6  12.Nxd4±  with a clear advantage.   Better is  10...Re8  but White still retains the better chances after  11.dxe5  Nxe5  12.Nfxe5  Bxe5  13.Nxe5  Qxe5  14.Re3⩲ }
