axb3 Qe7 11. Nf3
{ The knight has done its job on g5 and is now headed to c4.   11.Bd2  featued inGiri, A. - Carlsen, M. Norway Masters Blitz 2016 where Black played the careless  11...O-O-O ?!  castling straight into an attack after  12.b4!  Instead  @@StartFEN@@r3k2r/pppnqppp/1bp5/4p1N1/4P3/1P1P4/1PPB1PPP/R2Q1RK1 b kq - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  11...f6  would have been far stronger. }
11... f6
{ Black carries on with his standard plan of reinforcing e5 with ...f6 and later rerouting the d7 knight to e6. }
12. Nd2
{ The knight is about to land on c4 so Black should create a square for the bishop on a7. }
12... a6 13. Nc4 Ba7 14. Kh1
{ White steps out of the a7-g1 diagonal to enable the f4 break. This move was not covered in the Chessable course From Berlin to Rio by IM Piotr Nguyen and GM Lukasz Jarmula.  While Black's position remains solid, White's position is both objectively slightly better and easier to play. The lopsided 2.5/3 score in practice is good evidence. }
