8. c3
{ 8.O-O  is met by the immediate  8...Nf8  when Black quickly gets his knight to e6. }
8... Nb6 9. b4 Bd6 10. Nxd6+
{ is the superior knight move.   10.Na5  is another interesting possibility that has recently been tested in a few games.  10...O-O   10...c5  was played by Giri. While not an outright mistake, it's usually best not to commit to an early ...c6-c5 which later proved to be Giri's undoing. Please refer to the middlegame section for more details.  11.Be3  was played in the game 1/2 @@StartBracket@@43@@EndBracket@@-1/2 @@StartBracket@@43@@EndBracket@@ Anand,V @@StartBracket@@2753@@EndBracket@@-Leko,P @@StartBracket@@2663@@EndBracket@@ chess24. com INT 2020, when Black could have immediately reacted with  11...f5  with a balanced game. }
