{ is White's most flexible move, not committing the king to either flank. }
8... f6
{ Black slightly weakens his kingside in order to reinforce the center. This is a clear signal that White should start active operations on the kingside.   8...Re8  9.a4  transposes to 7...Re8 variation. }
9. Qe2 Re8 10. g4
{ is the most enterprising move. Starting with queenside castling was also possible. }
10... Nb6
