1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Bxc6 dxc6 6. Nbd2 O-O
{ This is Black's most popular and natural move. The king will most likely end up on the kingside, so Black may as well start with this move and only then decide where to place the queen and light-squared bishop. }
7. Nc4 Re8 8. a4 a5
{ is a logical move, stopping White's a-pawn dead in its tracks and preventing Na5. Notwithstanding, this pawn can become a weakness in the long run. }
