10... O-O 11. Nc3 Re8 { 11...c5  as usual, is met by  12.Nf5 } 12. Qf3
{ The queen is actively placed on f3, from where it supports active play on the kingside and eyes the weak c6 pawn. There's no need to prepare this move with h3 as ...Bg4 can simply be sidestepped.   A sample continuation is  12...h6  a logical move, preventing Bg5 before dropping the bishop back to f8.  13.Bf4  c5  14.Nf5  Bf8  15.Rad1⩲  While Black's position isn't easy to break down, all of White's pieces are superior to Black's counterparts. }
