7... Bg7 8. d5 Ne7 9. Bd3
{ is practically a novelty. It's been played in a couple of engine vs engine games, but has yet to be tested in OTB or correspondence games.   9.Bxd7+  is very reasonable and White's main move. It leads to King's Indian type positions, where exchanging the light-squared bishops is usually in White's favor as it hinders Black's kingside initiative. Nevertheless, White will be much faster on the queenside and Black's position is fairly cramped, so keeping another pair of minor pieces on the board is certainly logical. }
9... O-O 10. c4 h6
