14. Qb3 cxd5 15. exd5 { Annd here Black has to find the brilliant intermezzo }
15... e4
{ before taking on c5 in order to stay in the game. This is far from obvious! }
16. Bxe4 dxc5 17. Be3
{ A very tricky move, attempting to induce ...b6 which would take away this square from Black's queen.   17...b6  18.Bf4  is obviously better for White.   Remarkably, Black is able to bail out with  17...c4!  18.Qd1  Nd6  19.Bc2  And after another precise move  19...b5  20.axb5  Nxb5  21.Nxb5  Bxb5  22.d6!  While Black is objectively fine, his position is far from easy to handle in practice. }
