{ The Open Ruy Lopez is a first rate variation in the Spanish. Anand brought it into the limelight when he essayed it in the 1995 PCA Candidates against Kamsky and in the 1995 World Championship match versus Kasparov. Nowadays, this defense is played by a large subset of the world's elite such as Carlsen, So and Mamedyarov. With perfect play, Black is objectively equal everywhere but this doesn't mean White cannot pose problems in practical games. Black's main idea is to use use the time White will take to regain the pawn to gain a foothold in the center. }
6. d4 Be7
{ used to be popular all the way back in the 90s. It's very rare nowadays although a couple of super-GMs have played it on occasion. Mamedyarov used it successfully vs Aronian in the 2018 Batumi Olympiad and Magnus Carlsen also gave it a shot in the 2019 London Chess Classic with two draws against MVL. }
