{ is a position that arises pretty much by force when Black plays 6...Be7. We must play energetically to exploit our lead in development. If Black is given enough time to complete development, he'll be fine. }
11. Qe2
{ After extensive analysis, we concluded this is White's strongest move. The pressure on the e7 bishop rules out ...O-O and the plan is to quickly bring the queenside pieces into the game with Nc3, Bf4 and Rae1. }
11... f6
{ was recommended by IM Yuriy Krykun in the Chessable course Unleash the Bull. However, it does not equalize. }
12. Re3
{ White drops the rook back and is ready to play Nc3. Black's best is to undermine our center with }
12... c5 13. dxc5 Kf7
