13... exd4 14. cxd4 d5 15. Nbd2 O-O
{ Once again, White can enter a superior endgame after a forced series of trades starting with }
16. Nxe4 dxe4 17. Ng5
{ The double-attack on the e4 and f7 pawns forces 17...Qe7. } 17... Qe7 18. Qh5
h6 19. Nxf7 Rxf7 20. Bxf7+ Qxf7 21. Qxf7+ Kxf7 22. d5
{ is the whole point of the combination. Rather deep but very strong! } 22...
Bxe3 23. dxc6 { An important intermezzo! } 23... Bd4 24. cxb7 Bxb2 25. Rad1
Rxb7 26. Rxe4
{ This is already a success for White. Even though Black can hold with precise play, White can press for many moves and is the only side that can win. }
