20. e5 dxe5
{ I was surprised to find that in both games that reached this position, White took on c5. The only way to get an advantage is to capture the other pawn. }
21. dxe5 Nd5 22. Bxd5
{ Simple and effective. We eliminate Black's only active piece and are one move away from completing development with Rad1. }
22... Qxd5 23. Rad1 Be6 24. Ne4 Qb3 25. Qd2
{ Stockfish gives White a significant advantage in this position while Lc0 only offers White a slight pull. The truth is probably somewhere in between. White's position looks very advantageous to my human eyes. We have full control over the d-file, which Black can never challenge, and an excellent outpost on d6. An interesting plan is to play on the kingside with Nh4 followed by f4-f5. }
