13... Rf8 14. Re1 Ra8
{ is a typical idea. Black protects the a7 bishop before playing ...Bb7. } 15.
Nf3
{ The knight has done its job on g5 and returns to f3, reinforcing the d4 pawn in order to develop the b1 knight. }
15... Bb7 16. Nbd2 exd4
{ has been tried by several notable players, including Caruana, Ragger, and Fedoseev. I have a very hard time believing in this variation due to a fantastic exchange sacrifice later down the line. }
17. cxd4 Nb4
{ This was Black's main idea, trying to exploit White's lack of control over the d2 square as a consequence of Nbd2. This knight sortie also clears the way for ...c7-c5. }
18. Bg5 h6 19. Bh4 Nd3
{ All the OTB games so far have continued with  20.Re3  . Everyone missed the astounding exchange sacrifice }
20. Qc2 { played in a single correspondence game back in 2017. } 20... Nxe1 21.
Rxe1 c5 22. e5
{ This was all seen in the correspondence game½-½ @@StartBracket@@68@@EndBracket@@ Smirnov,B-Nenneman,D @@StartBracket@@2065@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2017. Black was able to hold with the help of a strong engine, but in a human encounter it's very hard to do so. }
