[Black "Why 15. Qd2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O b5 6. Bb3 Bc5 7. a4 Rb8 8. c3
d6 9. d4 Bb6 10. a5 Ba7 11. h3 O-O 12. Be3 exd4 13. cxd4 Nb4
{ is the absolute mainline of the Arkhangelsk. } 14. Nc3
{ We now see the point of delaying Nbd2, that is White can now develop the knight to a more active square. }
14... Bb7 15. Qd2
{ Novel and strong. At very high depth, the engines tend to prefer this over 15. Ng5 which is the current mainline. Truth be told, both lead to equality but @@StartBracket@@a@@EndBracket@@ Black's path to equality is far harder after the text and @@StartBracket@@b@@EndBracket@@ it's a novelty that is likely to surprise your opponents.   15.Ng5  is White's main continuation. The absolute mainline goes  15...Qe7  16.e5  dxe5  17.Nxf7  and now  17...e4!  as played in the high-profile game½-½ @@StartBracket@@44@@EndBracket@@ Vachier Lagrave,M @@StartBracket@@2767@@EndBracket@@-Caruana,F @@StartBracket@@2842@@EndBracket@@ Ekaterinburg 2020 is sufficient to maintain the balance. As usual, Caruana was extremely well prepared. White's best is  18.Ng5+!  Kh8  19.Ne6  but Black is objectively fine after  19...Rfc8=  This is still worth giving a shot in a practical game. I can't stress enough how well prepared Black must be to maintain the balance. }
15... c5
{ is the only move to stay within the realms of equality. All of Black's moves are pretty much forced and a single deviation is likely to be fatal. }
16. dxc5 dxc5 17. Rad1
{ It's very important to understand the differences between Rad1 and Rfd1.   After  17.Rfd1  Black can go for  17...Qe8  when we can't play  18.Bg5  due to  18...Nxe4  19.Nxe4  Qxe4  Now we don't have the option of playing Re1 @@StartBracket@@without allowing ...Qd3@@EndBracket@@. If the a-rook were on d1 and the kingside rook on f1, we could have played Rfe1 without allowing ...Qd3. Nuanced but important!   17.Rfd1  Qe8  18.e5  is no solution. After  18...Bxf3  19.exf6  Bxd1  20.fxg7  Bxb3  21.gxf8=Q+  Qxf8  22.Bh6  Qd8  23.Qf4  Qd4  it's White that needs to be precise to keep himself above water. The text avoids all these possibilities. }
