1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3
O-O 9. h3
{ In this chapter, we are going to examine all of Black's 9th move alternatives to the three mainlines, namely the Zaitsev with  9...Bb7  ,  the Chigorin with  9...Na5  ,  and the Breyer with  9...Nb8  . We will tackle the following options on move nine:   A@@EndBracket@@  9...a5  The Keres variation;   B@@EndBracket@@  9...Nd7  The Karpov variation;   C@@EndBracket@@  9...Be6  The Kholmov variation;   D@@EndBracket@@  9...Qd7  Smyslov variation;   E@@EndBracket@@  9...h6  Smyslov variation. @@StartBracket@@Yes, there are two variations named after the 7th World-Champion!@@EndBracket@@ }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "9th move alternatives"]
[Black "9...Rb8"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3
O-O 9. h3
{ This is the well-known Closed Spanish tabiya from which thousands upon thousands of games have been played. Many top players have ventured these waters and champions have been decided in the complexities of these structures. Mastering this structure is guaranteed to improve your chess understanding.   Black’s top three choices in this position are the Chigorin with  9...Na5  , the Breyer with  9...Nb8  and the Zaitsev with  9...Bb7  . In this chapter, we’ll examine all of Black’s other options on move 9. does have some other choices, which will be covered in this chapter. }
9... Rb8
{ This has been tried by some top level GMs such as Caruana, Anand, and Naiditsch to name a few. Nevertheless, it is not a good move as it allows White to take over the center undeterred. }
10. d4 exd4 11. cxd4 d5
{ is Black's most popular move. White can push the pawn as played by MVL to defeat Caruana, but it's even stronger to take on d5. }
12. exd5 Nxd5 13. Bxd5 Qxd5 14. Nc3
{ The knight comes out with tempo, driving Black's queen back and preparing d5 on the next turn. }
14... Qd8 15. d5 Na5 16. Bf4
{ White has a clear advantage. The d5 pawn affords the first player extra space, Black's c7 pawn is weak and the knight on a5 is misplaced. }
