1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3
O-O 9. h3
{ This is the well-known Closed Spanish tabiya from which thousands upon thousands of games have been played. Many top players have ventured these waters and champions have been decided in the complexities of these structures. Mastering this structure is guaranteed to improve your chess understanding.   Black’s top three choices in this position are the Chigorin with  9...Na5  , the Breyer with  9...Nb8  and the Zaitsev with  9...Bb7  . In this chapter, we’ll examine all of Black’s other options on move 9. does have some other choices, which will be covered in this chapter. }
9... Be6
{ The Kholmov variation was once popular in the 1980s, but it's seldomly seen these days. That being said, White still needs to know what to do to emerge with an advantage. }
10. d4
{ Logical and strong, taking over the center. White is now threatening to win on the spot with d4-d5. }
10... Bxb3 { Nothing else makes sense. } 11. axb3
{ is the correct recapture, opening up the rook on a1. } 11... exd4
{ This is Black's main and best move by far. The second player needs to open up the position to get any sort of play. }
12. cxd4 Nb4 13. d5
{ White gains space and prevents Black from playing ...d5 himself. } 13... c5
{ This is practically forced. Otherwise, the c7 pawn will remain backward and a big target. }
14. dxc6 Nxc6
{ 14...d5?!  weakens the d-pawn even more. After the following sample continuation  15.e5  Ne4  16.Nc3  Nxc3  17.bxc3  Nxc6  18.Qd3±  White is just better. The d5-pawn is a huge weakness. }
15. Nc3 h6 16. Bf4
{ White has a big advantage. The d6-pawn is a huge target, and the d5-square is a great outpost for the c3 knight.   A sample line runs  16...Re8  17.Bg3  with the idea Bh4xf6 to then establish a knight on d5.  17...Bf8  18.Nd4  Offering the trade of the knights. The more minor pieces come off the board, the more the d6 and d5 weaknesses will tell.  18...Nxd4  19.Qxd4  Qd7  20.Bh4±  White is not far away from winning here. Bxf6 is a big threat while Rad1 and Nd5 are also coming. Black is in big trouble. }
