{ The knight has reached its desired square. The tempo Black 'wasted' with ...h6 allowed White to achieve a perfect setup. }
13... Na5
{ Chigorin-like play, clearing the way for ...c5, is the only way to go. } 14.
Bc2 Nc4
{ Black delays c7-c5, keeping his position flexible and also transferring the knight to a better position. }
15. b3 Nb6
{ White has several options here. I like the immediate space gaining move } 16.
a4 bxa4 17. bxa4
{ Threatening a4-a5 to fix the a6-pawn. As such, it makes sense for Black to push his own pawn to a5. }
17... a5 18. Bd3
{ White is definitely for choice here as it's very hard to come up with a plan for Black. The first player can complete development with Be3, Qc2, and then look to expand with d4-d5 at an opportune moment. }
