{ And now we see the point of delaying the development of the b1 knight. It now pops out to a3 hitting the vulnerable b5 pawn. }
19... Qd7 20. Qb1
{ A fine maneuver. White lines up the queen against the weak b5 pawn, not giving Black any chances. }
20... Nxd5
{ 20...Kh8  is an interesting waiting move, avoiding the queen exchange after trade on bxc5 and Qxb5. Black would then have ...Qxd5.  21.c4!  A sizzling shot! Black's structure now crumbles.  21...Rxa3  22.Rxa3  Nxc4  23.Rd3  White securely holds everything.  23...Qxf5  24.Re2±  Covering f2 and threatening Rf3. Black doesn't have enough for the exchange. }
21. bxc5 dxc5 22. Qxb5 Qxb5 23. Nxb5
{ White is a clean pawn up and Black's e5 and c5 pawns are very weak. } *

