{ A very enterprising move, immediately starting active operations on the kingside.   A sample continuation goes  15...c4  16.b4  Nb7  17.Kh2  We let Black continue with his queenside expansion undeterred.  17...a5  18.Be3  Ra6  19.a4!  This is the real killer shot. All of a sudden, Black is busted.  19...Nxa4  20.Bxa4  bxa4  21.Na3±  White has sacrificed a pawn to completely neutralize Black's queenside play. The knight on a3 is an excellent blockader. White now has a free hand on the kingside, meaning Black is in big trouble! You can opt to train this sample line in the nextalternative variation. }
