{ first played by Kasimdzhanov against Smirin all the way back in 2006. } 16...
exd4 17. Rxe8 Qxe8 18. cxd4 Bxd5
{ all happened in the game ½-½ @@StartBracket@@30@@EndBracket@@ Kasimdzhanov,R @@StartBracket@@2672@@EndBracket@@-Smirin,I @@StartBracket@@2659@@EndBracket@@ Fuegen 2006. An improvement is }
19. Qxc7
{ simply grabbing the pawn. The c1 bishop may look passive at the moment, but it can come out to b2. Alternatively, White can drop the queen back to f4 to reinforce the f3 knight and then move the d2 knight. White is a pawn up and clearly better. }
