{ The whole point of our operation. The previous moves were designed to force Black to block the b7 bishop's path to our e4-pawn, allowing us to retreat the knight to f1 without having to play Ng3 right away. We can take advantage of this added flexibility by flicking in g2-g4 in a variety of lines, reaching favorable versions of the usual Breyer. The text hasn't had the best of reputations as it allows Black to break in the center with 15...d5. Correct, but we're going to see how to neutralize it 😉. }
