{ 18...Nf5  runs into  19.e6!  fxe6  20.Nxe6  Qd6  21.Nxg7  Kxg7  22.Rxe8  Rxe8  23.Nf3  axb4  24.axb4  Qxb4  25.Bb3±  with the idea Ra7. Despite being two pawns down, White has a big advantage due to the bishop pair and the discoordination in Black's camp. }
19. Nxf7 { A nice shot uncorked by Firouzja vs Andrew Tang. } 19... Qh4
{ is the best move, seen in the game0-1 @@StartBracket@@102@@EndBracket@@ Fedoseev,V @@StartBracket@@2678@@EndBracket@@-Tang,A @@StartBracket@@2538@@EndBracket@@ Chess.com INT 2020.   19...Qd7  was played by Tang in an earlier game against Firouzja. Alireza obtained a big advantage after  20.Ng5  Ne6  21.Nxe6  Qxe6  22.Ne4  and went on to win in1-0 @@StartBracket@@41@@EndBracket@@ Firouzja,A @@StartBracket@@3010@@EndBracket@@-Tang,A @@StartBracket@@2786@@EndBracket@@ Chess.com INT 2018. }
20. Re4 { is a strong improvement over Fedoseev's play. } 20... dxe4 21. Bxd4
{ threatening multiple discoveries such as Ng5+ and Nd6+. White is having all the fun here. }
