16... Qb6 17. Rc1
{ Qc2 was also possible but with Black's queen already committed to the queenside, preparing the c4 break is more precise. }
17... Nh5 18. Bf1
{ A typical prophylactic move when faced with the prospect of ...Nf4. } 18...
Nf4 19. c4
{ White is now threatening b3-b4 and c4-c5 gaining a lot of space. Black's only good way of preventing this is }
19... exd4 20. Nxd4 Ne5 21. Qc2
{ White enjoys a solid advantage thanks to the extra space and superior central control. Black's knight on f4 is very shaky. }
