{ is an interesting way of preventing the Marshall Gambit. The idea is to clarify the queenside pawn structure at an early stage and gain control over the c4 square, which can become a possible outpost for one of White's knights. }
8... d5
{ isn't supposed to work @@StartBracket@@spoiler alert: it doesn't!@@EndBracket@@. The move 8. a4 - aptly titled the Anti-Marshall - was played precisely to prevent this move. That didn't stop the ever creative Russian GM Daniil Dubov from essaying it a couple of times. Objectively, this line is very speculative and mainly played to try and catch White off-guard. }
