11. Bxe6 fxe6 12. Nbd2 Qe8
{ is a very logical move. Black scoots his queen over to g6, from where it puts pressure on White's kingside. Additionally, by vacating the d8 square, the e6 pawn can now easily be covered with ...Nd8.   12...Qb8!?  is another option that has the same idea.  13.Nb3  Nd8  14.d4  and leads to similar play as the text. }
