{ Black is trying to kick the bishop away, in which direction should White go? }
8. Ba4
{ Indeed! The bishop would be kicked again with d5 if it goes to c4 and Black gains the important tempo, which doesn't let us showcase our designed plan that can be seen after }
8... d5
{ 8...a5  is not worrisome as it doesn't really trap our bishop if we are fast enough to create our own play with  9.f5!  b5  Doesn't work:  10.Bb3  a4  11.fxg6+-  White comes in first! }
9. f5 { Black has nothing better than to take on f5. } 9... gxf5 10. exd5
{ Very important, even at the cost of a pawn, White must open up the position and try to finish the game as soon as possible. Closing down the position by taking back on f5 would not have been a good idea.   Following  10...Qxd5  11.Bb3  Qd8  12.Qe1+  Ne7  13.Bg5±  White has a very dangerous initiative. }
