Qh5+ g6 9. Qe2
{ White never had any ideas of taking on g6. The point of Qh5+ was to provoke weaknesses in Black's kingside. The dark-squares are now critically weak and the g6 pawn is a perfect hook for h4-h5 down the line.   9.Nxg6?!  should be avoided as it allows  9...Nf6  10.Qh6  Rg8  11.Ne5  Rxg2⇆  This is just unnecessary. Instead, we just retreat with our queen to attack the e4-pawn happy with the newly-provoked weaknesses in Black's camp. }
