25... Rf7
{ This position was reached in the game 1-0 @@StartBracket@@48@@EndBracket@@ Caruana, F @@StartBracket@@2822@@EndBracket@@ -Naroditsky,D @@StartBracket@@2621@@EndBracket@@ Chess.com INT 2020 where White played 26. Kg2. Can you find a better move? }
26. e5
{ A fantastic breakthrough that's not at all easy to find, especially in a rapid game!   26.Kg2  Qd8  27.Nh4  Qf8  28.Qxf8+  Rfxf8  29.f4  g5  30.Nhf5  Ng6  31.Nxd6  Nxf4+  32.Kf3  Rad8  33.Nb7  Rc8  34.Rh1  Ng6  35.Ke3  Rc7  36.Nd6  Rd8  37.Nh5  Kf8  38.Rf1  Ke7  39.Rxf6  Bxg4  40.hxg4  Rxd6  41.Rf5  Nh4  42.e5  Nxf5+  43.gxf5  Rh6  44.Bd1  Kf7  45.Bg4  Kf8  46.Ke4  Rg7  47.f6  Rf7  48.Kf5  1-0 @@StartBracket@@48@@EndBracket@@ Caruana,F @@StartBracket@@2822@@EndBracket@@ -Naroditsky,D  @@StartBracket@@2621@@EndBracket@@ Chess.com INT 2020 }
26... fxe5 { 26...dxe5  27.Ne4+-  wins as there's no stopping d5-d6. } 27. Ng5
Rg7 28. Nh5 { is an absolute killer move. Black has no defense. } 28... gxh5
29. Bxh7+ Kh8 30. Ne6 Bxe6 31. Bf5+ Kg8 32. Bxe6+ Kf8
{ 32...Rf7  33.f4+-  intending to blast open the f-file with fxe5 and bring the rook to f1 wins. }
33. Qf6+ Ke8 34. Qxg7 *

